==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|κεραμικός||potter's|sc=Polytonic|tr=keramikos|lang=grc}}, from {{term|κέραμος||potter's clay|sc=Polytonic|tr=keramos|lang=grc}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|æmɪk}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# made of material produced by the high temperature firing of inorganic, nonmetallic rocks and minerals.
#: ''A ceramic vase stood on the table.''

